{"name":"Arcane Background (Ritualist)","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p>Player characters don’t have Arcane Background Edges in <em>East Texas University</em>, but anyone can take a new skill called Occult (linked to Smarts) which acts as the arcane skill for any power. The only catch is that the character must have attempted a ritual at least once as a leader or participant before taking his first skill level in Occult. Characters can attempt to lead or participate in a ritual using Smarts –2 instead of Occult, but all Casting Modifiers are doubled!</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":""}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"Kzz0iKsauvHx8Iad"}
{"name":"Devout","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Devout students believe in a greater power, deity, or spirit, or perhaps just their own sense of self and willpower. They are typically religious, but don’t have to be. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Devout heroes add +2 to all </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle2\">opposed </span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Spirit rolls where their faith might come into play such as resisting evil powers (Dean’s call).</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"cg5RrKOfPydf5LBQ"}
{"name":"Filthy Rich","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he’s got more money than most.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Although wealthy by student standards, your money comes from your parents, a trust fund, or some other restricted</span> source.<br style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-size-adjust: auto;\"></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Filthy Rich students get a regular semester allowance of $1,500.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"tafjf0MiMb6r2uMr"}
{"name":"Local Favorite","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Some students were born and raised in Golan County, but this student is not only from the area but popular with the locals. He gets the best seats at hangouts in town and the locals are more willing to spill the dirt to him on at least some of the local scandals. Any randomly determined initial Reaction for an NPC local is always one level higher for this hero, and if the Dean thinks the Edge applies then predetermined Reactions may be one level higher as well. This Edge can only be taken during character creation.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"OViWc3WWC01kB9Rt"}
{"name":"Noble","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Noble is the equivalent of coming from a wealthy or notable family concerned about their public appearance.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; background-color: #dfe6f5;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the Rich or Filthy Rich Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-size-adjust: auto;\"></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"color: #191813; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Aristocrats add +2 to Persuasion when&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"color: #191813; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Networking&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"color: #191813; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">(see page 133) with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to Common Knowledge rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</span>&nbsp;<br style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-size-adjust: auto;\"></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The kid </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">is pressured to stay out of trouble and “keep his nose clean.” How this affects the student is up to the Dean, but visits from “Daddy” and local media attention should be expected.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"LXOB6wtnRxYJNowI"}
{"name":"Rich","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he&rsquo;s got more money than most.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Although wealthy by student standards, your money comes from your parents, a trust fund, or some other restricted</span> source.<br style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-size-adjust: auto;\" /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Rich students get a regular semester allowance of $1,000.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"R9V7aIMHFA5VTzJ8"}
{"name":"Test Taker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Some individuals do well on tests even when they study far less than most. Those with this Edge add a permanent +2 to their Academics secondary attribute.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"gKQmO1wA5olFtF8c"}
{"name":"Be a Zebra","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There’s protection in the herd! You gain a +2 to Parry if you are adjacent to at least one ally or fellow target (Dean’s call).</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"nXQH5gM6khCVxYoB"}
{"name":"Gunslinger","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The senior’s sidearm is like an extension of his body. He can disarm a cultist or shoot the smile off a chupacabra at 20 paces.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When using pistols gunslingers ignore –2 in total Shooting penalties regardless of the source (wounds, range, called shots etc.).</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Shooting d10+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"dZahyQz9jWuhNJEu"}
{"name":"Demon Slayer","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Demon slayers may come from an awakened lineage, a special blessing, or occasionally just coming in contact with the blood of a demon. Regardless of the source, demon slayers add +2 to Fear tests from demonic sources (demons themselves, their minions, or powers), and ignore the demon’s invulnerability to normal weapons.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"443jRu8PmVuBtnof"}
{"name":"Faithful","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This hero’s faith in something—whether it’s science, God, or whatever—is so strong supernatural creatures fear her.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Supernaturally evil creatures subtract 2 from any Trait roll directly affecting the character.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Devout, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"tKDKMakR215N885x"}
{"name":"Fearless","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You’re not actually fearless, but you’re as close as it gets. If you fail a Fear roll, the GM rolls a d12 for the Fright Table result instead of a d20.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Brave, Guts, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"OLWCvDFEHxxLmdbB"}
{"name":"Guts","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This cowgirl has stared the things that lurk in the dark right in the mug and learned to handle her fear. She ignores two points of Fear penalties for both her Spirit roll and any Fright Table result.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sophomore, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"IwN6ijwfw0Tb8DV8"}
{"name":"Multitasker","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This character excels at scheduling her time and interests. Each semester, she may choose two Extracurricular Activities instead of one, gaining the benefits and any drawbacks of both.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"NnYZHm3G0Nz2qgUP"}
{"name":"Sage","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Not only did this senior pay attention in class, he actually retained it—and most everything else he’s ever seen, read, or heard about.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The sage adds +2 to Investigation rolls and can make an Investigation roll without any source material (other than his memory) at a –2 penalty.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Smarts d10+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"XuIqG1QtgODpnghF"}
{"name":"Witch/Warlock","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There are plenty of good witches and warlocks out there. Hopefully, this hero remains one of them.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When casting a ritual (by the time you’re a Junior you’ll know what they are), she ignores up to 2 points of Casting Modifiers. This does not apply to other participants, who still roll with the usual penalties.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Occult d8"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"2NK7qRyk8bnl6FX2"}
{"name":"Aura Reader","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This Edge allows the student to read another person’s energy—or “aura.”</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">To do so, the character must be within ten feet (in person—video doesn’t work) and make a Spirit roll at –2. If the roll is successful, the character knows the target’s general emotional state (happy, sad, angry, nervous, etc.) and her overall health (sick, weak, strong, etc.). With a raise, she can identify specific health conditions, such as a concussion, spirit possession, Fatigue, cancer, diabetes, etc.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Failure results in a level of Fatigue and loss of the ability for 24 hours.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sophomore, Psychically Sensitive, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"2Y2PPg5yfsHEylbX"}
{"name":"Chosen","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The powers of good appreciate someone who stands up for what’s right, even when it’s hard. Sometimes they even pitch in and reward you for it.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When the character spends a Benny to re-roll a Trait test, he can re-roll twice and take the best of all the results.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Senior, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"jflBdtogviiinagr"}
{"name":"Danger Sense","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This Edge from </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Savage Worlds </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">gains Psychically Sensitive as a requirement.</span> &nbsp;</p>\n<p>Your hero can sense when something bad is about to happen. When rolling for <strong>Surprise</strong> (page 108), he adds +2 to his Notice roll to act in the first round. With a raise, he starts the encounter on Hold.</p>\n<p>In other situations not covered by the Surprise rules (a sniper shot, pit trap, poisoned drink, etc.), Danger Sense gives him a Notice roll at -2 (or +2 if a Notice roll is usually allowed) to detect the hazard and take appropriate action. If this was an attack and the hero makes his Notice roll, the foe doesn't get The Drop against him.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The +2 bonus from Psychically Sensitive applies to the Notice roll for Danger Sense (negating the normal –2 penalty) if the danger is from a supernatural creature or source.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Psychically Sensitive"}},"flags":{"journal-links":{}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"1SCZqoGBiz9QZ2Xl"}
{"name":"I See Dead People","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Either due to a traumatic event or spectral encounter, the character can see spirits. He ignores the invisibility effect of the ethereal Special Ability. The spirit can leave an area, but if it’s present, the hero can see it.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Aura Reader"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"VnCZZaQ8DUMr3ab3"}
{"name":"Medium","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can now hear your spirit guardian. In addition to making communication easier, the spirit guardian can act as a “translator” to speak with other spirits. Unlike </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">grave speak</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">, no spirit is summoned nor required to answer truthfully, though spirits are more favorably disposed to the character. The hero has +2 Persuasion checks when dealing with spirits.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Spirit Guardian"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"kh9RviNYNOC8B5l6"}
{"name":"Memorized Ritual","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This character has memorized one ritual and no longer needs to have the written text to perform it. This Edge can be taken multiple times but only once per ritual.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Occult d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"EIBwBlbsNre9u6SV"}
{"name":"Precognitive Flashes","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You occasionally see visions of the future. They happen quickly, are almost always vague and hard to decipher, but they usually warn of some dangerous event that might save your life—and your friends as well. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per session, when it seems most appropriate, the Dean will describe a likely upcoming event or scene. The future is mutable, so it may not come to pass, but it should be a likely course, or perhaps the vision depicts a path </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">not </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">to take and won’t unless your student ignores the warning.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Make a Spirit roll immediately after seeing the vision—the Dean may modify this depending on the severity of the vision. If the roll is failed, your character is Fatigued for the next eight hours. This might manifest as violent nosebleeds, migraines, or simple weariness.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Psychically Sensitive, Danger Sense, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"9sLewqsEWbHTrmcm"}
{"name":"Psychically Sensitive","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Something about this student gives her an affinity for paranormal energies and beings.<br></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">She adds +2 to all rolls made to sense or communicate with supernatural beings. Of course the downside is that if such a creature knows the person is receptive they’re more likely to actually attempt contact. That may not actually be something you’ll want to happen at ETU.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"m1WWuJe1aWXqNeau"}
{"name":"Psychometry","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When touching an object (non-living thing), your character may attempt to gain impressions or visions linked to its past.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">To do so, make a Spirit roll at –2. Success grants a basic impression of an important or traumatic event centered around the object, and a raise provides more details.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">For example, a success might flash the image of a knife being plunged into a body. A raise reveals the knife’s wielder wore a ring with a cat’s eye stone.</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Junior, Aura Reader, Spirit d10, Notice d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"iqwX50VOLWzLun0b"}
{"name":"Spirit Guardian","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The spirit of a departed friend or loved one looks out for you. It could be your last roommate mauled by a werewolf or even the dog you had in the Sixth Grade.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">You can see the spirit and it can hear you, but it cannot communicate other than with basic gestures. A </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">grave speak </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">ritual does allow communication with the spirit.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The guardian provides a +2 bonus to opposed rolls with other spirits as it helps fend them off, but it can also serve more subjectively at the Dean’s whim, guiding the hero away from trouble, to friends in need, etc. The spirit is bound to the character and cannot travel farther away than its Spirit die type in inches unless prevented by a ward (use the standard ghost stats on page 91, adapted by the Dean for the specific spirit).</span></p>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Freshman, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","_id":"ShxaxtBqMbUb9t6v"}
